sub_title: Project of life and English teacher
summary: I am fascinated by the human mind and how it works. My experience with psychology contributed a lot in this regard. Nevertheless, it was my study of philosophy which gave meaning to my learning. On the other hand, I am interested in education. I have given a few lectures on memory and learning in a Brazilian public school and have taught English for one year in a language school. At the present moment, I am investigating the relationship between humans and nature by visiting indigenous tribes, learning about herbal medicine and writing essays. I believe that we can contribute to future generations by exploring meaningful forms of education and bringing forth philosophical thought, emotional intelligence and a better relationship with the natural environment.
